      "file": "sas_codebase/docs/functional_spec.md",
      "sections": [
        {
          "title": "CTX-2024-001 ADaM Pipeline \u2014 Functional Specification",
          "level": 1,
          "line_start": 1,
          "datasets": [],
          "columns": [],
          "bullets": [],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": " **Study**: CTX-2024-001, Phase 2 dose-ranging **Document version**: 1.3 (2024-02-28) **Owner**: Statistical Programming"
        },
        {
          "title": "1. Purpose",
          "level": 2,
          "line_start": 10,
          "datasets": [],
          "columns": [],
          "bullets": [],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": " This document specifies the analysis dataset (ADaM) derivations for the CTX-2024-001 safety analyses. It is the contract between Stats Programming and the Reporting team. The CSR shells reference dataset names and column"
        },
        {
          "title": "2. Pipeline overview",
          "level": 2,
          "line_start": 17,
          "datasets": [
            "adae",
            "adsl",
            "ae_clean",
            "ae_incidence",
            "ae_summary",
            "dm_clean",
            "raw.ae",
            "raw.dm",
            "site_lookup"
          ],
          "columns": [
            "ADAE",
            "ADSL",
            "AE_CLEAN",
            "AE_INCIDENCE",
            "AE_SUMMARY",
            "DM_CLEAN"
          ],
          "bullets": [],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": " Five SAS programs produce the ADaM datasets and summary tables:  | # | Program            | Output         | Depends on          |"
        },
        {
          "title": "3. Inputs",
          "level": 2,
          "line_start": 32,
          "datasets": [],
          "columns": [],
          "bullets": [],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": ""
        },
        {
          "title": "3.1 RAW.DM \u2014 Demographics",
          "level": 3,
          "line_start": 34,
          "datasets": [],
          "columns": [],
          "bullets": [],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": "One row per subject (in principle; see \u00a76.1 on duplicates).  Columns: `USUBJID, AGE, SEX, RACE, ARM, SITEID, BRTHDTC, RFSTDTC, RFENDTC, RECORDCREATEDT` "
        },
        {
          "title": "3.2 RAW.AE \u2014 Adverse Events",
          "level": 3,
          "line_start": 41,
          "datasets": [],
          "columns": [
            "AESEV"
          ],
          "bullets": [],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": "Multiple rows per subject. Severity (`AESEV`) is captured on the CRF as free text and must be standardized. See \u00a74.2.  Columns: `USUBJID, AETERM, AESEV, AESER, AESTDTC, AEENDTC`"
        },
        {
          "title": "3.3 RAW.SITE_LOOKUP \u2014 Site reference",
          "level": 3,
          "line_start": 47,
          "datasets": [],
          "columns": [],
          "bullets": [],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": "Site descriptors. Joins to DM on site identifier.  Columns: `SITE_ID, SITE_NAME, SITE_COUNTRY, SITE_REGION` "
        },
        {
          "title": "4. Derivation rules",
          "level": 2,
          "line_start": 52,
          "datasets": [],
          "columns": [],
          "bullets": [],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": ""
        },
        {
          "title": "4.1 Demographics cleaning (`DM_CLEAN`)",
          "level": 3,
          "line_start": 54,
          "datasets": [],
          "columns": [
            "AGE",
            "AGEGRP",
            "ARM_DECODE",
            "BRTHDTC",
            "RECORDCREATEDT",
            "RFSTDTC",
            "SEX_DECODE",
            "USUBJID"
          ],
          "bullets": [
            {
              "line": 56,
              "text": "Convert all ISO date strings to SAS dates."
            },
            {
              "line": 57,
              "text": "Where `AGE` is missing, derive from `BRTHDTC` and `RFSTDTC` using"
            },
            {
              "line": 59,
              "text": "Apply formats from `formats.sas` to derive `SEX_DECODE`, `ARM_DECODE`,"
            },
            {
              "line": 61,
              "text": "Compute `TRTDURD = RFENDT - RFSTDT + 1`."
            },
            {
              "line": 62,
              "text": "**Deduplication**: where multiple records exist for one `USUBJID`,"
            }
          ],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": " - Convert all ISO date strings to SAS dates. - Where `AGE` is missing, derive from `BRTHDTC` and `RFSTDTC` using   365.25 days/year and FLOOR."
        },
        {
          "title": "4.2 AE cleaning (`AE_CLEAN`)",
          "level": 3,
          "line_start": 65,
          "datasets": [],
          "columns": [
            "AESEQ",
            "AESTDTC",
            "AETERM",
            "MAX_AESEV",
            "MILD",
            "MODERATE",
            "SEVERE"
          ],
          "bullets": [
            {
              "line": 67,
              "text": "Convert dates as above."
            },
            {
              "line": 68,
              "text": "Standardize severity to `MILD` / `MODERATE` / `SEVERE`. Accepted raw"
            },
            {
              "line": 74,
              "text": "Drop records where `AESTDTC` or `AETERM` is missing."
            },
            {
              "line": 75,
              "text": "Assign `AESEQ` within subject, ordered by start date then term."
            },
            {
              "line": 76,
              "text": "Derive `MAX_AESEV` per subject (worst severity observed)."
            }
          ],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": " - Convert dates as above. - Standardize severity to `MILD` / `MODERATE` / `SEVERE`. Accepted raw   values: `'MILD'`, `'MODERATE'`, `'MOD'`, `'SEVERE'`, `'SEV'`,"
        },
        {
          "title": "4.3 ADSL derivations",
          "level": 3,
          "line_start": 78,
          "datasets": [
            "dm_clean",
            "site_lookup"
          ],
          "columns": [
            "DM_CLEAN",
            "RFSTDT",
            "SITE_LOOKUP"
          ],
          "bullets": [
            {
              "line": 80,
              "text": "Left join `DM_CLEAN` to `SITE_LOOKUP` on site identifier."
            },
            {
              "line": 81,
              "text": "**Safety population (SAFFL)**: subject has `RFSTDT` populated."
            },
            {
              "line": 82,
              "text": "**ITT population (ITTFL)**: `SAFFL = 'Y'` and `ARM \u2260 'PLACEBO'`."
            }
          ],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": " - Left join `DM_CLEAN` to `SITE_LOOKUP` on site identifier. - **Safety population (SAFFL)**: subject has `RFSTDT` populated. - **ITT population (ITTFL)**: `SAFFL = 'Y'` and `ARM \u2260 'PLACEBO'`."
        },
        {
          "title": "4.4 ADAE derivations",
          "level": 3,
          "line_start": 84,
          "datasets": [
            "adsl",
            "ae_clean"
          ],
          "columns": [
            "ADSL",
            "AE_CLEAN",
            "USUBJID"
          ],
          "bullets": [
            {
              "line": 86,
              "text": "Inner join `AE_CLEAN` to `ADSL` on `USUBJID`."
            },
            {
              "line": 87,
              "text": "**Treatment-emergent flag (TRTEMFL)**: `'Y'` if AE start date is on"
            },
            {
              "line": 90,
              "text": "**On-treatment flag (ONTRTFL)**: AE start date within"
            },
            {
              "line": 92,
              "text": "Compute `ASTDY = AESTDT - RFSTDT + 1`."
            }
          ],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": " - Inner join `AE_CLEAN` to `ADSL` on `USUBJID`. - **Treatment-emergent flag (TRTEMFL)**: `'Y'` if AE start date is on   or after first dose. *(See \u00a76.3 \u2014 implementation uses cohort"
        },
        {
          "title": "4.5 Safety summaries",
          "level": 3,
          "line_start": 94,
          "datasets": [
            "ae_incidence",
            "ae_summary"
          ],
          "columns": [
            "AE_INCIDENCE",
            "AE_SUMMARY"
          ],
          "bullets": [],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": " `AE_SUMMARY`: counts of treatment-emergent AEs by `ARM \u00d7 SEVERITY`, with serious-AE counts. "
        },
        {
          "title": "5. Formats",
          "level": 2,
          "line_start": 103,
          "datasets": [],
          "columns": [],
          "bullets": [],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": " Defined in `config/formats.sas`. All programs `%include` this file. "
        },
        {
          "title": "6. Known issues / open items",
          "level": 2,
          "line_start": 107,
          "datasets": [],
          "columns": [],
          "bullets": [],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": ""
        },
        {
          "title": "6.1 DM duplicates (resolved by dedup logic)",
          "level": 3,
          "line_start": 109,
          "datasets": [],
          "columns": [],
          "bullets": [],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": "A 2023 CRF amendment caused some subjects to appear twice in the raw extract. The dedup step in \u00a74.1 handles this. "
        },
        {
          "title": "6.2 Vendor B severity codes (deferred)",
          "level": 3,
          "line_start": 113,
          "datasets": [
            "ae_summary"
          ],
          "columns": [
            "AESEV_STD",
            "AE_SUMMARY"
          ],
          "bullets": [],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": "~5% of AE records arrive with `GRADE 1`/`GRADE 2`/`GRADE 3` style codes. These are NOT mapped in v1.3. Their `AESEV_STD` will be blank and they will appear in the \"blank severity\" row of `AE_SUMMARY`. Tracked as SP-184. Decision deferred to data review meeting."
        },
        {
          "title": "6.3 \"First dose\" vs \"randomization\" date for TRTEMFL",
          "level": 3,
          "line_start": 119,
          "datasets": [],
          "columns": [],
          "bullets": [],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": "The TRTEMFL definition in \u00a74.4 says \"first dose date\". The current implementation uses the cohort-level latest randomization date as a proxy. The medical monitor accepted this for v1.3 but flagged it for review in v1.4 (SP-227)."
        },
        {
          "title": "6.4 Site lookup join",
          "level": 3,
          "line_start": 125,
          "datasets": [
            "site_lookup"
          ],
          "columns": [
            "SITEID",
            "SITE_ID"
          ],
          "bullets": [],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": "DM stores `SITEID` as character (`'01'`, `'02'`...). The SITE_LOOKUP extract delivers `SITE_ID` as numeric (1, 2...). The PROC SQL join relies on SAS implicit type conversion. Works in SAS, but flagged during code review as a portability concern."
        },
        {
          "title": "7. Out of scope (v1.3)",
          "level": 2,
          "line_start": 131,
          "datasets": [],
          "columns": [],
          "bullets": [
            {
              "line": 133,
              "text": "Vital signs, labs, ECG processing"
            },
            {
              "line": 134,
              "text": "Concomitant medications"
            },
            {
              "line": 135,
              "text": "Death and discontinuation rates"
            },
            {
              "line": 136,
              "text": "Subgroup analyses beyond age group and sex"
            }
          ],
          "open_issues": [],
          "body_preview": " - Vital signs, labs, ECG processing - Concomitant medications - Death and discontinuation rates"
        }
      ]
